The paper proposes a new training scheme for neural networks that improves both generalization and acceleration abilities. The experiments are conducted on deep convolutional neural networks for classification tasks, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for training neural networks, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
